content.description: Low start on two pinches. Move up into a long right facing sloper. From here, you can work into Phallacy, or straight up through underclings and pockets for a more independent line at the same grade. Highball finish.
content.protection: A couple of pads - a fall from the top could be bad.
content.location: Starts left of the black streak.

content.description: Sit start on segmented holds. Work up and right.
content.location: On small cliff band left of the Big Spud boulder.

content.description: Sit start in small cave on underclings. Go up and left through the delicate slab.
content.location: Left side of the Big Spud boulder.

content.description: Sit start in the small cave on the right side. Left hand pinch on the face, right hand on a small knot on the arete. Work up and left into Phallacy.
content.protection: A couple pads - a fall from the top could be bad.
content.location: Right side in a small overhang/cave.

content.description: Sit start left side on a pair of undercling pinches. A hard move off the ground leads into a rightward traverse into Yukon Gold. A fun line straight up awaits an FA to someone willing to clean the upper section.
content.protection: Several pads or a spotter. Traverses quite a bit into a highball finish.

content.description: Sit start on the obvious namesake feature. Make a big throw to the large potato jug, work straight up through the black streak, and over the committing highball slab.
content.protection: Several pads - a fall from the top could be serious.
content.location: Straight up through the obvious black streak.
